They are still finding some of the books of his library in the most remote countries.

16:25.104 --> 16:26.605
He should have given them here.

16:26.966 --> 16:28.428
It was better.

16:28.448 --> 16:29.028
It's a pity.

16:29.489 --> 16:39.220
Because when he died, part of the library was bought by the Signore di Padova.

16:39.402 --> 16:41.965
the Carraresi, the family of Carraresi.

16:41.985 --> 16:46.631
Then Pada was conquered by Visconti, who carried the library to Milan.

16:46.651 --> 16:54.580
Then Milan was conquered by the French, who takes part of it to France, partly dispersed the collection.

16:55.080 --> 16:59.025
And so they are everywhere now, unfortunately.

16:59.065 --> 17:02.870
So in 1527, where was the building that was built for the books?

17:02.990 --> 17:03.751
This building here?

